      "message": "[warning] Line 142: đźźˇ Suggestions - If the app backgrounds before the FCM token is available, `deactivateRunnable` restores accounts and returns because `pushToken \u003d\u003d null`, but the `pushToken` setter does not re-arm background deactivation when the token later arrives. That leaves accounts active until the next foreground/background lifecycle transition. When a valid token is set while the app is not visible, schedule the deactivation path again after registering the token.\n\n```suggestion\nif (token !\u003d null \u0026\u0026 mPreferencesService.settings.enablePushNotifications) {\n    mAccountService.setPushNotificationToken(token.second)\n    backgroundHandler.post {\n        if (!isAppVisible()) scheduleBackgroundDeactivation()\n    }\n} else {\n    mAccountService.setPushNotificationToken(\"\")\n}\n```",
