      "message": "[Critical] Line 69: đź”´ Critical Issues - `appInForeground` is computed after starting `PushForegroundService`. A foreground service can make the process report `IMPORTANCE_FOREGROUND`, so an incoming call push received while the UI is backgrounded may skip `onBackgroundPushReceived()`, leaving proxy accounts inactive and missing the call. Use process lifecycle/UI visibility, or snapshot visibility before starting the foreground service.\n\n```suggestion\nval app \u003d JamiApplication.instance as JamiApplicationFirebase?\nval appInForeground \u003d app?.isAppVisibleForPushHandling() ?: isAppInForeground()\n\nif (isCallNotification) {\n    try {\n        val intent \u003d Intent(this, PushForegroundService::class.java)\n        startForegroundService(intent)\n    } catch (e: Exception) {\n        Log.w(TAG, \"Failed to start foreground service for push notification\", e)\n    }\n}\n```",
